snatch each torturing vision ere it flies
me thither quickly take my flight
a favourite and a final seat
this altered frame , Which youthful graces lately did adorn
me still the same , Thy once gay friend , thus hapless and forlorn
by ruddy health embrowned , Now pale

added terrors fraught , And my torn heart
thee formed of tenderness and truth
my weapon in thy noble breast Thy dying hand clasped mine , with feeble power , And to thy mangled bosom fondly pressed

cool reason in his breast preside , His opening wisdom had not bloomed in vain
